trans-unit.source: Specifies settings for <see cref="T:System.ServiceModel.NetHttpBinding" />.
trans-unit.target: Especifica la configuración de <see cref="T:System.ServiceModel.NetHttpBinding" />.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.ServiceModel.NetHttpBinding> is a binding designed for consuming HTTP or WebSocket services and uses binary encoding by default.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.ServiceModel.NetHttpBinding> es un enlace diseñado para consumir servicios HTTP o WebSocket y usa la codificación binaria de forma predeterminada.

trans-unit.source: Note: WebSockets are only supported on Windows 8.
trans-unit.target: Nota: WebSockets solo se admiten en Windows 8.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.ServiceModel.NetHttpBinding> will detect whether it is used with a request-reply contract or duplex contract and change its behavior to match - it will use HTTP for request-reply and WebSockets for duplex (only on Windows 8).
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.ServiceModel.NetHttpBinding> detectará si se usa con un contrato de solicitud-respuesta o dúplex y cambiar su comportamiento para que coincida; usará HTTP de solicitud-respuesta y WebSockets para los dúplex (solo en Windows 8).

trans-unit.source: This behavior can be overridden by setting the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.WebSocketTransportUsage> property to one of the following values:
trans-unit.target: Este comportamiento se puede invalidar estableciendo la <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.WebSocketTransportUsage> propiedad en uno de los siguientes valores:

trans-unit.source: WhenDuplex- This is the default value and behaves as described above.
trans-unit.target: WhenDuplex: es el valor predeterminado y se comporta como se describió anteriormente.

trans-unit.source: Never - This prevents WebSockets from being used.
trans-unit.target: Nunca: evita que se use WebSockets.

trans-unit.source: Attempting to use a duplex contract with this setting will result in an exception.
trans-unit.target: Si se intenta usar un contrato dúplex con este valor se producirá una excepción.

trans-unit.source: Always - This forces WebSockets to be used even for request-reply contracts.
trans-unit.target: Siempre: obliga a usar WebSockets incluso para los contratos de solicitud-respuesta.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.ServiceModel.NetHttpBinding> supports reliable sessions in both HTTP mode and WebSocket mode.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.ServiceModel.NetHttpBinding> admite sesiones confiables en modo HTTP y en modo WebSocket.

trans-unit.source: In WebSocket mode sessions are provided by the transport.
trans-unit.target: En el modo WebSocket, el transporte proporciona las sesiones.
